<h1>Popularity of Online Stores</h1>
<p>Many people used to enjoy weekly walks to the store with their families. However, what changed?</p>
<p>Online orders were popular, but became mainstream after massive lockdowns.</p>
<p>In 2020, Covid has arrived and caused millions to stay home. How did that impact stores?</p>
<p>In order not to go out of business, shops moved to online shopping and deliveries,</p>
<p>with enchanced quality and e-commerce sites, companies were able to sustain their profits.</p>
<p>Moreover, some companies have made improvements and now are in better shape.</p>
<p>Since Covid, online shopping has became mainstream and a part of every day life, and </p>
<p>up to today, customers find online shopping fun and convinient. Do you?</p>
<p>All you do is calmly choose the stuff you want to get while chilling on the </p>
<p>soft couch, and scrolling through your shopping cart. The next day, you get</p>
<p>a fancy package next to your door. How wonderful! And moreover, you save on car fuel!</p>
